-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 12:34AM EDT
-- None



June 24 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* U.S. specialty media buyout firm Providence Equity Partners LLC is in discussions to buy struggling Australian broadcaster Ten Network Holdings <TEN.AX>, a source with knowledge of the discussions told Reuters on Tuesday. [ID:nL4N0P50AG]  * Portugal's second-largest listed bank, Millennium BCP <BCP.LS>, is preparing to raise 2 billion euros ($2.72 billion) of capital to help it repay state loans faster, sources familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL6N0P4612]  * Italy's Banco Popolare <BAPO.MI> is considering delaying a sale of bad debt until after the summer since the offers it has received are not satisfactory, a source close to the matter said on Monday. [ID:nL6N0P45FY]  * French bank BNP Paribas SA <BNPP.PA> is likely to pay $8 billion to $9 billion as part of a potential settlement with U.S. authorities over violations of sanctions, according to a person familiar with the matter. [ID:nL6N0P41GW]  * Loral Space & Communications Inc's <LORL.O> efforts to sell itself and its main asset, Telesat Holdings Inc, broke down after the company failed to agree on a potential $7 billion deal with the buyer group, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL2N0P41EL]  * Bahrain-based investment firm Investcorp Bank BSC <INVB.BH> is looking to sell Berlin Packaging LLC in a deal that could value the U.S. packaging distribution company at around $1.3 billion, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0OS1CT]  * German roofing company Braas Monier <IPO-BMBG.F> will likely sell its shares at between 24 euros and 24.50 euros ($32.58-$33.26) apiece in a stock market listing later this week, two sources familiar with the transaction said on Monday. [ID:nWEB00OPM]  * Amazon.com Inc <AMZN.O> has resumed preorders of movie discs from Time Warner Inc's <TWX.N> Warner Bros Studio as the companies are close to resolving a pricing dispute, the Wall Street Journal reported citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0P50A6]  * U.S. authorities have sought information from Dean Foods Co <DF.N> and Clorox Co <CLX.N> in connection with an insider-trading investigation of billionaire investor Carl Icahn, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0P44SM]  * Goldman Sachs has been hired by Shire <SHP.L> as the London-listed drug maker confronts a takeover offer, people briefed on the matter told the New York Times. (http://nyti.ms/1iAzfyy)  * Monsanto Co <MON.N>, the world's largest seed company worth $64 billion, recently explored a takeover of $34 billion Swiss rival Syngenta AG <SYNN.VX> in a transaction that would have allowed the U.S. firm to move its tax location to Switzerland, people familiar with the matter told Bloomberg. (http://bloom.bg/T3k44E)  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]